Look-Up Classes to Add:

  

Garrett
Spring 2016
04:54 am
To add a class, check the box in front of the CRN and click Register at the bottom of the page.
A select code of C identifies a closed class. If a class is closed but has waitlist seats available listed under WL REM, copy the CRN and click here to add yourself to the waitlist for that class on your Add Classes Worksheet. SR indicates you are not eligible to add the class. To determine why you would not be eligible to add a class check your registration status by clicking here.

Drill through course hyperlinks to display required pre-requisites, restrictions or needed approvals.

Seat Availability: The “Rem” column shows the number of seats remaining. However, if a class has students on a waiting list (“WL Act” column), those remaining seats are open only to students on the waiting list.

Reserved Seats: These seats, designated in the "Rsrvd Rem" column, represent seats that are open. However, these seats may be reserved for new student orientation attendees. You'll know this if you see "Reserved Seats for Orientation". If a course "Rem" is equal to "Rsrvd Rem" and you are a continuing student, you will likely not be able to register for these seats.

"Cap" is inclusive of "Rsrvd Rem" seats, NOT in addition. (i.e., 20 Cap & 2 Rsrvd Rem means that only 18 seats are available outside of the reserve)
